That's a feature.  The incremental compiler will partially compile classes, and insert a runtime exception in the function with the compile error:

ex: the code below prints "Hello" when there are program arguments but throws a runtime exception when there are not:

Exception in thread "main" java.lang.Error: Unresolved compilation problem: 
	GoodBye cannot be resolved

	at ex.RunAway.f2(RunAway.java:16)
	at ex.RunAway.main(RunAway.java:8)

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		if (args.length>0) {
			f1();
		} else {
			f2();
		}
	}

	private static void f1() {
		System.out.println("Hello");
	}
	private static void f2() {
		sysout(GoodBye);
	}

